@@IniWriteBool
<GROUP RegistryandInifiles.Inifiles>
Summary:
  Writes a boolean key to an ini file.
Description:
  IniWriteBool writes a single boolean key to the specified section in the
  specified ini file. If the function fails it raises an exception.
Parameters:
  FileName - The fully qualified filename of the ini file.
  Section - The section in the ini file to which to write a value
  Line - The name of the key to write
  Value - The value to write
See also:
  IniReadBool
  IniReadInteger
  IniReadString
  IniWriteInteger
  IniWriteString
Donator:
  John C Molyneux
