@@IniReadBool
<GROUP RegistryandInifiles.Inifiles>
Summary:
  Reads a boolean key from an ini file.
Description:
  IniReadBool reads a single boolean value within the specified section from the
  specified ini file. If the function fails it returns the default value False.
Parameters:
  FileName - The fully qualified filename of the ini file.
  Section - The section in the ini file from which to read a value
  Line - The name of the key to read
Result:
  The key within section, default value returned on failure is False.
See also:
  IniReadInteger
  IniReadString
  IniWriteBool
  IniWriteInteger
  IniWriteString
Donator:
  John C Molyneux
